\begin_layout Section
Supported types in Properties
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
APB can handle propertiesof different types, not only Strings, in particular:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Strings (
\family typewriter
java.lang.String
\family default
 class)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Any java primitive type (boolean, char, byte, short, int, long, float &
 double)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The wrappers of the primitive types (
\family typewriter
java.lang.Boolean
\family default
, 
\family typewriter
java.lang.Character
\family default
, etc).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Enum types.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Lists (
\family typewriter
java.util.List
\family default
 class) of any of the above types.
 For example:
\family typewriter
 List<String>
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Inner objects that contain any of the supported types, including other 
\family typewriter
inner
\family default
 objects.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We'll discuss the last two cases in more detail in the following section.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the simpler cases APB will take care of converting the value to a String
 using the toString method for the type when expanding the value inside
 another String (using the '$' notation).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When overriding the property from the command line (-D option) APB will
 take care of converting the specified String value to the appropiate type
 using the most suitable convention for the type.
 In particular when you override a boolean property it would take 'true'
 as the intended value (-Dxxx is equivalent to -Dxxx=true), in the case
 of enumerations the conversion is case insensitive.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
